BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Other
DESCRIPTION:\nChapter Advisor Training equips advisors to confidently and 
 effectively support sorority and fraternity chapters through a focus on r
 ole clarity\, student development\, and organizational safety. The traini
 ng emphasizes understanding advisor responsibilities and boundaries withi
 n university\, council\, and national structures\; building coaching and 
 communication skills to guide Generation Z student leaders and strengthen
  chapter operations\; and proactively addressing risk\, culture\, and cri
 sis situations. Advisors learn to apply developmentally appropriate advis
 ing strategies\, identify and respond to potential risks\, and foster inc
 lusive\, healthy chapter cultures by modeling culturally aware\, values-d
 riven practices aligned with institutional and organizational expectation
 s.\n \n\nHosted by: Sorority and Fraternity Life\n\nAdditional Informatio
 n can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12459056
DTEND:20260807T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260508T023829Z
DTSTART:20260807T160000Z
GEO:39.170590;-86.509780
LOCATION:Cedar Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CANCELLED
SUMMARY:OSFL Advisor Training
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12459056
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12459056
X-HOSTS:Sorority and Fraternity Life
END:VEVENT
